title: For Sale:  CZ 52 7.62X25 Tokarev - Price Drop!
postcontent:
Very lightly used - includes rare picatinny rail on front. about 100 rounds included and a takedown manual. Cash only please no trades. Local face-to-face in Sherwood.
Amazing round 
This pistol cartridge packs a real punch. Surplus ammunition can have velocities ranging from 1450 fps up to 1650 fps from pistols and Sub-guns/rifles can have velocities higher than that do to longer barrels. I’ll get into that further down with my Chrono data. Shooting 85 grn projectiles in the surplus ammunition gives an energy level of 397 ft lbs up to 514 ft lbs of energy from a pistol. To give you a comparison using new Winchester ammunition:

7.62x25  85grn       velocity: 1647 fps   energy: 512 ft lbs.
9mm     115grn       velocity: 1190 fps   energy: 361 ft lbs.  
40S&W  165grn       velocity: 1060 fps   energy: 411 ft lbs.
45acp    230grn       velocity:   880 fps   energy: 396 ft lbs

This powerful little bottle-necked cartridge is a direct relation of and an improvement on the 7.63x25 Mauser cartridge. They are so close the you may use the 7.63x25 Mauser ammunition in firearms chambered for the Tokarev round.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Parkerizing tanks / lids / chemicals - NEW
postcontent:
NEW parkerizing tanks & checmicals for sale or trade: I have for sale 2 new/never used stainless steel parkerizing tanks with lids and ½” drain valves. I bought these thinking I was going to learn how to parkerize guns but never got around to it so these have just been sitting collecting dust. Also included with this is 1 gallon of Zinc Phosphate Parkerizing Solution and 1 gallon of Post Treatment Solution, both new and unopened. Each gallon of chemical is concentrated and gets mixed with 4 gallons of water for 5 total gallons of each, which is the capacity of each tank. 

I paid right around $450 shipped to the door for the pair of tanks/lids plus around $125 shipped to the door for the chemicals. I have around $575 wrapped up in this but I will sell everything as a set for $400 cash or $450 trade value. Located in Dublin and you must be willing to meet in the Dublin area for the sale. Trades considered would possibly be 12 ga. shotguns, rifles, handguns in 9mm (no Hi-Point, Kel-Tec, or Jennings), ammo in 9mm (brass cased), .22LR (high velocity only), .223 (40-52 grain, brass), .308 (155-168 grain, brass). Not interested in bows, crossbows, or black powder.

Here is the description of the tanks from the manufacturer:

6"x6"x40", pure 304 Stainless Steel. Tank, cover, and Stainless Steel ball valve are included. 

We are proud to offer the very best Parkerizing Tanks in the industry. They are cut and formed out of pure 304 stainless steel. Handles are formed right into the ends. All edges of these tanks are hemmed, so there are no exposed sharp edges. Feel free to handle these tank with your bare hands! 

The tanks are TIG welded using supreme skill and elaborate tooling. The outside of the welds are treated and polished to reveal the beauty of the stainless steel and show the excellence of the weld. We maintain complete passivation inside the weld during manufacturing. Please look at the last picture taken of the inside of the weld, you will see that it remains brilliant and shiny. If you see a weld in stainless steel that is black or rust colored inside this means that proper provisions were not taken and rust and breakdown will start immediately when your liquid is applied.
